e%20court%20of%20Harjeet%20Singh%20Jaspal%2C%20Additional%20Chief%20Metropolitan%20Magistrate%2C%20was%20hearing%20the%20matter%20to%20decide%20if%20charges%20need%20to%20be%20framed%20against%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublic%20prosecutor%20Atul%20Srivastava%20urged%20the%20court%20to%20frame%20the%20charges%20against%20Singh%20and%20also%20against%20co-accused%20Vinod%20Tomar%20in%20relation%20to%20offences%20mentioned%20in%20the%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20chargesheet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsexual-harassment-case-enough-evidence-to-put-brij-bhushan-on-trial-delhi-police-tell-court%2Farticle67184319.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%201%2C000-page%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpictures-phone-location-other-evidence-show-brij-bhushan-allegedly-making-advances%5C%22%3Echargesheet%3C%2Fa%3E%20accuses%20Singh%20of%20offences%20under%20Sections%20354%20(assault%20or%20criminal%20force%20to%20woman%20with%20intent%20to%20outrage%20her%20modesty)%2C%20354A%20(sexual%20harassment)%2C%20and%20354D%20(stalking)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%20The%20chargesheet%20was%20filed%20on%20June%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESrivastava%20dismissed%20the%20submissions%20to%20the%20court%20by%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20Rajiv%20Mohan%2C%20by%20calling%20them%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20meritorious%E2%80%9D.%20Mohan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fwrestlers-sexual-harassment-case-touching-a-woman-without-sexual-intent-is-no-offence-brij-bhushan-tells-court%2Farticle67176695.ece%5C%22%3Ehad%20told%20the%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Chugging%20or%20touching%20a%20woman%20without%20sexual%20intent%20is%20not%20an%20offence%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20he%20only%20hugged%20the%20wrestlers%20as%20he%20took%20pride%20in%20their%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20someone%20he%20knew%20for%20many%20years%20and%20have%20mentored%20them.%20Winning%20a%20medal%20was%20a%20moment%20of%20pride%20for%20the%20country%20and%20that%20hug%20was%20just%20an%20expression%20of%20his%20happiness.%20This%20is%20why%20we%20maintain%20that%20he%20had%20no%20intent%20of%20sexual%20harassment%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mohan%20had%20said%20in%20defence%20of%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESrivastava%20also%20objected%20to%20Mohan%E2%80%99s%20submission%20that%20a%20Delhi%20court%20does%20not%20have%20territorial%20jurisdiction%20for%20offences%20committed%20outside%20India.%20The%20latter%20had%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20alleged%20offences%20by%20Singh%20%E2%80%93%20as%20mentioned%20in%20the%20charge%20sheet%20%E2%80%93%20took%20place%20outside%20India%2C%20in%20Mongolia%20in%202016%2C%20in%20Indonesia%20in%202018%2C%20and%20in%20Kazakhstan%20in%202019.%20He%20had%20also%20argued%20that%20for%20a%20Delhi%20court%20to%20try%20such%20offences%2C%20prior%20approval%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20should%20have%20been%20taken%2C%20which%20he%20said%2C%20was%20not%20obtained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20public%20prosecutor%20argued%20that%20the%20court%20will%20have%20jurisdiction%20to%20put%20Singh%20on%20trial%20as%20the%20offences%20in%20question%20were%20partly%20committed%20in%20Delhi.%C2%A0Referring%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgement%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F79805163%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAllowing%2520the%2520appeal%2520vide%2520its%2C8%2520of%2520the%2520POCSO%2520Act.%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ESartaj%20Khan%20vs%20the%20State%20of%20Uttarakhand%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20a%20criminal%20appeal%20filed%20in%202018%2C%20the%20public%20prosecutor%20submitted%20in%20the%20court%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6.qua%20submissions%20made%20by%20the%20defence%20in%20reference%20to%20Section%20188%20of%20the%20CrPC%2C%20it%20is%20submitted%20that%20the%20bar%20of%20Section%20188%20is%20applicable%20when%20the%20offence%20is%20committed%20outside%20India%20in%20its%20entirety%20and%20not%20otherwise%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20went%20on%20to%20point%20out%20that%20since%20the%20matter%20fell%20under%20Section%20354%20(assault%20or%20criminal%20force%20to%20a%20woman%20with%20intent%20to%20outrage%20her%20modesty)%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20with%20recourse%20to%20Section%20468(3)%20of%20the%20CrPC%2C%20there%20can%20be%20no%20questions%20on%20the%20bar%20of%20limitation%20as%20submitted%20by%20the%20defence%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20particular%20section%20of%20the%20CrPC%20deals%20with%20the%20period%20of%20limitation%20in%20relation%20to%20offences%20which%20may%20be%20tried%20together%2C%20which%20shall%20be%20determined%20with%20reference%20to%20the%20offence%20which%20is%20punishable%20with%20the%20more%20severe%20punishment%20or%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%20the%20most%20severe%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESrivastava%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20report%20of%20the%20oversight%20committee%20of%20WFI%20which%20exonerated%20Singh%20does%20not%20bar%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20the%20court%20to%20try%20him.%20He%20said%20called%20it%20a%20mere%20departmental%20enquiry%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20court%20is%20duty-bound%20to%20only%20study%20the%20material%20on%20record%20in%20the%20strict%20brackets%20of%20prima%20facie%20scrutiny%20and%20a%20mini-trial%20cannot%20be%20conducted%20at%20this%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691832607000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F31193332%2FFhgUhThaEAEOJTAfinal.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fenough-evidence-to-try-brij-bhushan-singh-in-sexual-harassment-case-delhi-police-tells-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20public%20prosecutor%20urged%20the%20court%20to%20frame%20charges%20against%20the%20BJP%20MP.%20He%20also%20dismissed%20Singh's%20submission%20in%20the%20court%20that%20he%20'had%20no%20sexual%20intent'%