ens-world-cup-quarter-final-england-v-columbia-follow-live-12938464%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwomens-world-cup-quarter-final-england-v-columbia-follow-live-12938464%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwomens-world-cup-quarter-final-england-v-columbia-follow-live-12938464%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Bill%20Proposes%2010-Year%20Jail%20For%20Hit-And-Run%2C%207%20For%20Rash%20Driving%20Deaths%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20effort%20to%20curb%20hit-and-run%20cases%2C%20the%20government%20has%20proposed%20a%20new%20provision%20as%20part%20of%20its%20overhaul%20of%20criminal%20laws%20in%20the%20country.%20A%20section%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%20which%20is%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20provides%20for%20a%20jail%20term%20of%20up%20to%2010%20years%20for%20drivers%20who%20escape%20from%20the%20scene%20after%20an%20accident%20or%20fail%20to%20report%20the%20incident%20to%20the%20police%20or%20a%20magistrate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20104(2)%20of%20the%20proposed%20law%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BWhoever%20causes%20death%20of%20any%20person%20by%20doing%20any%20rash%20or%20negligent%20act%20not%20amounting%20to%20culpable%20homicide%20and%20escapes%20from%20the%20scene%20of%20incident%20or%20fails%20to%20report%20the%20incident%20to%20a%20Police%20officer%20or%20Magistrate%20soon%20after%20the%20incident%2C%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20of%20either%20description%20of%20a%20term%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20ten%20years%2C%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20also%20proposed%20a%20significantly%20longer%20jail%20term%20for%20death%20due%20to%20rash%20and%20negligent%20driving%20not%20amounting%20to%20culpable%20homicide.%20Section%20104(1)%20of%20the%20Sanhita%20proposes%20a%20jail%20term%20of%20up%20to%20seven%20years%20as%20opposed%20to%20two%20years%20under%20Section%20304A%20of%20the%20IPC.%20Both%20sections%20also%20provide%20for%20fines%20being%20slapped%20on%20the%20offenders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoad%20accidents%20claimed%20over%201.5%20lakh%20lives%20in%202021%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highways.%20The%20report%20said%20a%20total%20of%204.12%20lakh%20road%20accidents%20occurred%20in%20the%202021%20calendar%20year%2C%20which%20claimed%201.54%20lakh%20lives%20and%20left%203.84%20lakh%20people%20injured.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20pointed%20out%20that%20while%20road%20accidents%20decreased%20by%208.1%25%20compared%20to%202019%20and%20injuries%20went%20down%20by%2014.8%25%2C%20fatalities%20rose%20by%201.9%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20cases%20of%20dowry%20death%2C%20the%20Sanhita%20retains%20the%20same%20wording%20and%20punishment%20as%20the%20IPC.%20Section%2079%20of%20the%20proposed%20code%20provides%20for%20a%20jail%20term%20of%20not%20less%20than%20seven%20years%2C%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20imprisonment%20for%20life.%20This%20is%20the%20same%20as%20Section%20304B%20of%20the%20IPC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHome%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20introduced%20three%20bills%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20yesterday%20to%20overhaul%20the%20British-era%20criminal%20laws.%20The%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20is%20proposed%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya.%20All%20three%20bills%20have%20been%20referred%20to%20a%20Standing%20Committee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691832300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-01%2Fbh5lk67_car-accident-generic-unsplash-650_625x300_24_January_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-criminal-laws-dowry-death-new-bill-proposes-10-year-jail-for-hit-and-run-7-for-rash-driving-deaths-4292099%22%2C%22