ative%20memory%20bias.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20shortage%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Funited-airlines-passenger-economy-business-class-san-francisco-taiwan-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estories%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Funited-airline-passenger-arrested-grabbed-woman-leg-2023-7%3Finline-endstory-related-recommendations%3D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eairline%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Funruly-passenger-jumped-emergency-exit-and-hid-to-avoid-arrest-2023-7%3Finline-endstory-related-recommendations%3D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassengers%3C%2Fa%3E%20misbehaving%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-newark-telaviv-turns-back-passenger-sat-crew-area-2023-4%3F_gl%3D1*o3tjsr*_ga*MzYzNDc5ODk4LjE2NzU5NzM5ODE.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5MTcwOTc0Ny4xNTYuMS4xNjkxNzA5ODM5LjU4LjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisrupting%20flights%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-charged-over-flight-attendant-assault-restrained-by-fellow-passengers-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattacking%20flight%20attendants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20just%20generally%20causing%20chaos%20on%20board%20%E2%80%94%20leading%20many%20to%20wonder%20when%20people%20got%20so%20out%20of%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20are%20among%20the%20majority%20of%20Americans%20who%20truly%20believe%20people%2C%20in%20general%2C%20are%20collectively%20getting%20worse%2C%20you%20may%20be%20suffering%20from%20%26quot%3BThe%20Illusion%20of%20Moral%20Decline%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D90059b4af95e9128266322cb7f6bc6b7d91878efdb8271dfa0c269fbc4ac6825%26postID%3D64d554621a8ef1cb670f3d23%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-023-06137-x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENature%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%20was%20aptly%20titled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20which%20analyzed%20new%20and%20historical%20survey%20data%2C%20found%20that%20people%20around%20the%20world%20and%20of%20all%20ages%20believe%20that%20morality%20is%20declining%2C%20and%2C%20in%20the%20US%20at%20least%2C%20have%20believed%20so%20for%20at%20least%2070%20years.%20%26quot%3BUS%20Americans%20have%20been%20reporting%20moral%20decline%20at%20the%20same%20rate%20for%20as%20long%20as%20researchers%20have%20been%20asking%20them%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20paper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudy%20author%20Adam%20Mastroianni%2C%20an%20experimental%20psychologist%20and%20author%20of%20the%20blog%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.experimental-history.com%2Fp%2Fthe-illusion-of-moral-decline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExperimental%20History%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esurveys%20the%20paper%20analyzed%20showed%20a%20significant%20majority%20of%20Americans%20believed%20morality%20was%20declining%2C%20regardless%20of%20when%20the%20surveys%20were%20given.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Gallup%20poll%20conducted%20in%201949%2C%2078%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20believed%20the%20human%20race%20was%20getting%20worse%20when%20it%20came%20to%20moral%20conduct.%20Another%20Gallup%20poll%20from%202019%20similarly%20found%2077%25%20of%20people%20believed%20moral%20values%20in%20the%20US%20were%20getting%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20true%20for%20the%20old%20and%20the%20young%20and%20for%20conservatives%20and%20liberals.%20Interestingly%2C%20survey%20data%20also%20suggested%20people%20believed%20the%20moral%20decline%20began%20around%20the%20time%20of%20their%20birth%2C%20regardless%20of%20when%20they%20were%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Mastroianni%20said%20the%20survey%20data%20suggests%20there%20hasn't%20actually%20been%20moral%20decline%20%E2%80%94%20just%20a%20consistent%20perception%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMy%20whole%20life%2C%20I've%20heard%20people%20complain%20about%20the%20demise%20of%20human%20goodness.%20%26quot%3BUsed%20to%20be%20you%20didn't%20have%20to%20lock%20your%20doors%20at%20night!%26quot%3B%20etc.%20Is%20this%20just%20a%20vocal%20minority%2C%20or%20do%20most%20people%20believe%20this%3F%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ETurns%20out%2C%20it's%20most%20people.%20177%20surveys%2C%20N%20%3D%20220%2C772.%20Here's%20a%20sample%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FgdL8aM5Jrd%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FgdL8aM5Jrd%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Adam%20Mastroianni%20(%40a_m_mastroianni)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fa_m_mastroianni%2Fstatus%2F1666482107403890688%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJune%207%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20evidence%20suggests%20morality%20is%20not%20declining%2C%20even%20though%20most%20think%20it%20is%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20surveys%20asked%20Americans%20questions%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20often%20do%20you%20encounter%20incivility%20at%20work%3F%20Were%20you%20treated%20with%20respect%20all%20day%20yesterday%3F%20How%20would%20you%20rate%20the%20state%20of%20moral%20value%20today%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20there%20is%20in%20fact%20this%20decline%20that%20people%20believe%20in%2C%20we%20should%20be%20able%20to%20find%20it%20somewhere%20in%20these%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20Mastroianni%20told%20Insider%2C%20noting%20that%20instead%2C%20the%20answers%20to%20these%20questions%20have%20largely%20remained%20the%20same%20over%20time.%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20see%20these%20lines%20go%20down%20over%20time%2C%20and%20instead%2C%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%20we%20find%20flat%20lines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGallup%20polling%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20asked%20Americans%20annually%20how%20they%20would%20rate%20the%20current%20state%20of%20moral%20value%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20every%20year%20people%20gave%20low%2C%20but%20consistent%20ratings.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20they%20did%20not%20think%20people%20in%20the%20US%20had%20high%20morals%20but%20rated%20the%20amount%20of%20morality%20the%20same%20every%20year.%20If%20morality%20were%20actually%20declining%2C%20that%20rating%20should%20decrease%20over%20time%2C%20and%20yet%20it%20does%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20morality%20declining%2C%20there's%20actually%20some%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20that%20people%20have%20higher%20morals%20than%20in%20the%20past.%20The%20study%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3Bobjective%20indicators%20of%20immorality%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20like%20murder%2C%20rape%2C%20and%20slavery%20%E2%80%94%20have%20decreased%20over%20time%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20not%20what%20one%20would%20expect%20if%20honesty%2C%20kindness%2C%20niceness%2C%20and%20goodness%20had%20been%20decreasing%20steadily%2C%20year%20after%20year%2C%20for%20millennia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMastroianni%20noted%20another%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F362089532_Did_cooperation_among_strangers_decline_in_the_United_States_A_cross-temporal_meta-analysis_of_social_dilemmas_1956-2017%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20published%20last%20year%2C%20that%20looked%20at%20%26quot%3Beconomic%20games%26quot%3B%20that%20social%20scientists%20conduct%20in%20labs%20in%20which%20people%20are%20asked%20to%20make%20decisions%20and%20given%20a%20financial%20incentive.%20The%20decisions%20typically%20involve%20choosing%20to%20do%20something%20that%20benefits%20yourself%20or%20benefits%20the%20collective%20group%20in%20the%20lab.%20The%20paper%20looked%20at%20studies%20conducted%20from%201956%20to%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20they%20expected%20to%20find%20is%20that%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20choose%20the%20greedy%20option%20today%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20past.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20found%20the%20opposite.%20People%20were%2010%20percentage%20points%20more%20likely%20to%20choose%20the%20generous%20option%2C%26quot%3B%20Mastroianni%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWe%20found%20140%20surveys%20(N%20%3D%2012%20million)%20where%20people%20were%20asked%20multiple%20times%20about%20the%20current%20state%20of%20morality%20around%20them.%20We%20found%20strong%20evidence%20of%20no%20change%20over%20time.%20For%20instance%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FSarhSipHQv%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FSarhSipHQv%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Adam%20Mastroianni%20(%40a_m_mastroianni)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fa_m_mastroianni%2Fstatus%2F1666482131185573889%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJune%207%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%3ESo%20why%20do%20we%20feel%20like%20everyone%20is%20getting%20worse%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20likely%20a%20host%20of%20reasons%20why%20humans%20consistently%20feel%20like%20morality%20is%20declining%2C%20but%20the%20study%20suggests%20two%20well-established%20psychological%20phenomena%20are%20combining%20to%20produce%20that%20perception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20humans%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20encounter%20information%20about%20strangers%20that%20is%20negative.%20That%20could%20be%20in%20the%20form%20of%20news%20media%2C%20like%20all%20the%20stories%20about%20disrespectful%20behavior%20on%20airplanes%2C%20or%20in%20the%20form%20of%20plain%20old-fashioned%20gossip.%20The%20second%20is%20the%20biased%20memory%20effect%2C%20in%20which%20%26quot%3Bthe%20badness%20of%20bad%20memories%20fades%20faster%20than%20the%20goodness%20of%20good%20memories%2C%26quot%3B%20Mastroianni%20said%2C%20meaning%20you%20may%20remember%20the%20past%20as%20better%20than%20it%20actually%20felt%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20if%20you%20get%20dumped%20at%20a%20high%20school%20dance%20it%20may%20be%20devastating%20when%20it%20happens%2C%20but%2020%20years%20later%20you%20might%20look%20back%20on%20it%20as%20a%20funny%20story.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20positive%20memory%20of%20your%20high%20school%20dance%2C%20it's%20likely%20to%20stay%20positive%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20potential%20explanation%20for%20the%20illusion%20of%20morality%20decline%20could%20simply%20be%20the%20number%20of%20people%20in%20the%20world%20interacting%20is%20increasing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20you%20open%20up%20different%20ways%20for%20people%20to%20relate%20to%20one%20another%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20you%20create%20new%20opportunities%20for%20people%20to%20be%20mean%20to%20one%20another%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20Mastroianni%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20rate%20of%20people%20being%20mean%20to%20one%20another%20on%20social%20media%20in%201985%20was%20zero%20because%20it%20didn't%20exist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20in%20the%20case%20of%20air%20travel%2C%20it%20may%20be%20true%20that%20the%20sheer%20number%20of%20rude%20interactions%20is%20increasing%20as%20more%20and%20more%20people%20are%20flying%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20has%20reported%20an%20increase%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fgraphics%2F2023%2F08%2F08%2Fairline-unruly-passenger-increasing%2F70520620007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunruly%20passengers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20pandemic%20mask%20mandates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20does%20not%20necessarily%20mean%20the%20rate%20of%20those%20interactions%20is%20increasing%2C%20or%2C%20even%20if%20it%20was%2C%20that%20it%20would%20be%20indicative%20of%20any%20sort%20of%20broader%20decline%20in%20morality%20society-wide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20totally%20possible%20that%20there%20are%20pockets%20where%20things%20get%20worse%2C%20other%20pockets%20where%20things%20get%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Mastroianni%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20there%20were%20some%20kind%20of%20major%20overall%20trend%2C%20we%20would%20be%20able%20to%20spot%20it%20somewhere%20in%20this%20big%20data%20set%2C%20and%20we%20just%20don't%20see%20it%20anywhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmorals-not-declining-us-people-just-think-they-are-study-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691831641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d56e0a7e9149001aa470f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmorals-not-declining-us-people-just-think-they-are-study-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Americans%20believe%20people%20are%20getting%20worse%2C%20but%20they've%20thought%20that%20for%20decades%20and%20the%20evidence%20may%20not%20be%20on%20their%20side%2C%20new%20study%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bu