%20Aadmi%20Party-led%20government%2C%20has%20seen%20strong%20opposition%20from%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%20The%20opposition%20alliance's%20MPs%20had%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20parliament%20when%20it%20was%20put%20to%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHome%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20had%20defended%20the%20government's%20proposed%20law%2C%20which%20overrides%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20order%20on%20who%20controls%20bureaucrats%20in%20the%20national%20capital.%C2%A0After%20an%20eight-year%20tussle%20between%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20government%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20ruled%20that%20the%20elected%20government%20is%20the%20boss%20of%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20ordinance%20refers%20to%20the%20order%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20which%20says%20parliament%20has%20the%20right%20to%20make%20laws%20on%20any%20issue%20related%20to%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi.%20There%20are%20provisions%20in%20the%20Constitution%20that%20allow%20the%20centre%20to%20make%20laws%20for%20Delhi%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Shah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20bill%20was%20passed%2C%20Delhi%20Chief%20Minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20tweeted%20the%20bill%20only%20sought%20to%20%26quot%3Benslave%26quot%3B%20the%20people%20of%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20was%20passed%20after%20a%20division%20in%20which%20131%20MPs%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20legislation%20and%20102%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20(DPDP)%20Bill%20was%20passed%20by%20a%20voice%20vote%20amid%20sloganeering%20by%20Opposition%20members%20over%20the%20Manipur%20issue.%20Some%20of%20the%20amendments%20sought%20by%20the%20Opposition%20were%20defeated%20by%20voice%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20includes%20a%20provision%20to%20impose%20up%20to%20Rs%20250%20crore%20penalty%20for%20data%20breaches%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20curb%20misuse%20of%20individuals'%20data%20by%20online%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Opposition%20had%20alleged%20the%20law%20will%20turn%20the%20country%20into%20a%20surveillance%20state.%20Critics%20fear%20feared%20allowing%20processing%20personal%20data%20without%20consent%20in%20nine%20broad%20instances%20could%20have%20serious%20implications%20for%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExemptions%20to%20the%20state%20and%20a%20contentious%20clause%20giving%20broad%20exemptions%20for%20some%20companies%20have%20also%20sparked%20concerns.%20The%20centre%20had%20previously%20introduced%20the%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20in%202019%20but%20it%20was%20withdrawn%20last%20year%20after%20scrutiny%20by%20a%20parliamentary%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20had%20expressed%20concerns%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsurveillance-of-citizens-editors-guilds-on-data-protection-bill-4274650%5C%22%3Ecertain%20provisions%20of%20the%20proposed%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20they%20can%20have%20an%20adverse%20impact%20on%20press%20freedom.%20In%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20Guild%20said%20it%20creates%20an%20enabling%20framework%20for%20surveillance%20of%20citizens%2C%20including%20journalists%20and%20their%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Section%2036%20of%20the%20law%2C%20the%20Guild%20said%2C%20the%20government%20can%20ask%20any%20public%20or%20private%20entity%20(data%20fiduciary)%20to%20furnish%20personal%20information%20of%20citizens%2C%20including%20journalists%20and%20their%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Registration%20of%20Births%20and%20Deaths%20(Amendment)%20Act%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Fndtv-explains-registration-of-births-and-deaths-amendment-bill-716194%5C%22%3Epaves%20the%20way%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20enabling%20digital%20birth%20certificates%20-%20which%20will%20become%20the%20only%20conclusive%20age%20proof%20and%20can%20be%20used%20as%20a%20single%20document%20for%20numerous%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20has%20provisions%20for%20allowing%20the%20birth%20certificate%20to%20be%20used%20for%20admission%20to%20educational%20institutions%2C%20issuing%20driving%20licence%2C%20registration%20of%20marriage%2C%20appointment%20to%20a%20government%20job%20and%20availing%20food%20welfare%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Jan%20Vishwas%20(Amendment%20of%20Provisions)%20Act%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmonsoon-session-of-parliament-jan-vishwas-bill-to-reduce-35-000-compliances-decriminalise-3-400-offences-4212149%5C%22%3Eseeks%20to%20promote%20ease%20of%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20decriminalising%20minor%20offences%20through%20amendments%20in%20183%20provisions%20of%2042%20Acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%20converts%20several%20fines%20to%20penalties%2C%20meaning%20that%20court%20prosecution%20is%20not%20necessary%20to%20administer%20punishments.%20It%20also%20removes%20imprisonment%20as%20a%20punishment%20for%20many%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691825520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Fqharjlh_arvind-kejriwal-vk-saxena_625x300_08_June_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-services-act-and-data-protection-act-become-laws-after-president-draupadi-murmus-nod-4291913%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20today%20gave%20assent%20to%20four%20bills%20passed%20during%20the%20stormy%20monsoon%20session%20of%20the%20parliament.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-services-act-and-data-protection-act-become-laws-after-president-draupadi-murmus-nod-4291913%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-services-act-and-data-protection-act-become-laws-after-president-draupadi-murmus-nod-4291913%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F