oreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D313a78999096da35c9fad0c31d414745b11d84ddce18c48e74b945c89efa9be8%26postID%3D64d6f3dd837033154c8b4ed0%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs42003-023-04986-w%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECommunications%20Biology.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20distinction%20between%20fully%20aquatic%20whales%20is%20made%20because%20not%20all%20ancient%20whales%20were%20fully%20aquatic%20%E2%80%94%20before%20the%20Basilosauridae%2C%20some%20whale%20ancestors%20walked%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fscience-nature%2Fwhales-once-walked-along-the-coasts-of-north-america-180979027%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereporting%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Smithsonian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20named%20in%20part%20%26quot%3BTut%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20ancient%20Egyptian%20Pharaoh%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcurse-tutankhamun-king-tut-pharoah-mummy-tomb-cause-fungi-2023-8%3F_gl%3D1*inv65g*_ga*MzIwMjM2OTE4LjE2ODY1OTY2MTY.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5MTgwOTcyOC4xNDcuMS4xNjkxODEwMjYzLjU4LjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETutankhamun%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%26quot%3BKing%20Tut%2C%26quot%3B%20who%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-epilepsy-kill-king-tut-2012-9%3F_gl%3D1*1khtgyl*_ga*MzIwMjM2OTE4LjE2ODY1OTY2MTY.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5MTgwOTcyOC4xNDcuMS4xNjkxODEwMTk0LjU3LjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edied%20at%2019%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20since%20researchers%20believe%20the%20specimen%20found%20had%20also%20not%20yet%20reached%20full%20maturity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasilosauridae%20are%20usually%20found%20in%20Egypt%2C%20according%20to%20the%20scientists'%20findings%2C%20and%20the%20T.%20rayanensis%20was%20discovered%20roughly%2025%20miles%20from%20the%20Wadi%20El-Hitan%20World%20Heritage%20Site%2C%20which%20the%20findings%20say%20is%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20productive%20fossil%20whale%20sites.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20discovery%20of%20the%20new%20basilosaurid%20whale%2C%20Tutcetus%20rayanensis%2C%20has%20brought%20about%20a%20substantial%20shift%20in%20our%20understanding%20of%20cetacean%20life%20histories%20during%20the%20Eocene%20epoch%2C%26quot%3B%20lead%20study%20author%20Mohammed%20S.%20Antar%2C%20a%20paleontologist%20at%20the%20Mansoura%20University%20Vertebrate%20Paleontology%20Center%20in%20Egypt%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F08%2F10%2Fworld%2Fmini-whale-fossil-basilosaurid-scn%2Findex.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520reconstruction%2520depicts%2520Tutcetus%2520rayanensis%2Cabout%252041%2520million%2520years%2520ago.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%20email%20to%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAntar%20told%20CNN%20that%20the%20T.%20rayanensis%20may%20have%20%26quot%3Bundergone%20faster%20developmental%20processes%20than%20previously%20believed%2C%20suggesting%20a%20diverse%20range%20of%20growth%20strategies%20within%20this%20group%2C%26quot%3B%20differentiating%20it%20from%20other%20members%20of%20its%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20incomplete%20fossil%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study%2C%20researchers%20determined%20the%20T.%20rayanensis%20is%20one%20of%20the%20oldest-yet%20discovered%20whale%20fossils%20across%20the%20globe%20%E2%80%94%20but%20another%20study%20author%20doesn't%20think%20that%20will%20be%20true%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErik%20R.%20Seiffert%2C%20a%20coauthor%20of%20the%20study%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20said%20to%20CNN%20there's%20a%20chance%20scientists%20will%20be%20able%20to%20discover%20even%20more%20ancient%20and%20fully-aquatic%20whales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20phylogenetic%20analysis%20suggests%20that%20the%20transition%20to%20a%20fully%20aquatic%20lifestyle%20likely%20occurred%20a%20few%20million%20years%20earlier%20than%20the%20age%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3ETutcetus%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20we%20do%20not%20yet%20have%20any%20fossil%20evidence%20that%20conclusively%20documents%20these%20predicted%20earlier%20forms%2C%26quot%3B%20Seiffert%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAntar%20and%20the%20MUVP%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%2C%20sent%20outside%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eregular%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebusiness%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fegyptian-paleontologists-bottlenose-dolphin-mansoura-university-41-whale-king-tut-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691816760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d6ff301f51cc001968459a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fegyptian-paleontologists-bottlenose-dolphin-mansoura-university-41-whale-king-tut-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dubbed%20%26quot%3BTutcetus%20rayanensis%26quot%3B%20by%20researchers%2C%20the%20species%20is%20the%20smallest%20known%20member%20of%20the%20extinct%20family%20basilosauridae.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Sebastian%20Cahill)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A308%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fegyptian-paleontologists-bottlenose-dolphin-mansoura-university-41-whale-king-tut-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Suhana%20gives%20Rs%201000%20to%20a%20street%20vendor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691816575000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102669088%2Cimgsize-34730.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fe