.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fstreaming%2Fwomens-world-cup-live-stream-free-how-to-watch-australia-vs-france-2023%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scientists%20found%20a%20new%20sea%20creature%20with%2020%20'arms'%20and%20named%20it%20after%20a%20strawberry%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222985%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Promachocrinus%20Feather%20Star%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d6e14a5e5d5a00195cc16e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221657%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20preserved%20Antarctic%20strawberry%20feather%20star%2C%20or%20Promachocrinus%20fragarius.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Greg%20W.%20Rouse%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20discovered%20a%20new%20species%20of%20feather%20stars%20with%2020%C2%A0%26quot%3Barms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20species%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Antarctic%20feather%20stars%20group%20and%20is%20broadly%20related%20to%20starfish.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EScientists%20named%20their%20discovery%20after%20a%20strawberry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20trawling%20the%20ocean%20near%20Antarctica%20uncovered%20a%20new%20species%20that%20looks%20haunting%20in%20photos%20%E2%80%94%20but%20named%20it%20after%20a%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Antarctic%20strawberry%20feather%20star%20is%20a%20sea%20creature%20with%2020%20so-called%20%26quot%3Barms%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20some%20bumpy%2C%20some%20feathery%20%E2%80%94%20and%20can%20altogether%20be%20up%20to%20eight%20inches%20long%2C%20Greg%20Rouse%2C%20a%20marine%20biology%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20San%20Diego%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERouse%20co-authored%20the%20paper%20on%20the%20new%20species%20with%20researchers%20Emily%20McLaughlin%20and%20Nerid%20Wilson%2C%20publishing%20their%20findings%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.publish.csiro.au%2FIS%2FIS22057%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInvertebrate%20Systematics%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20alien-like%20creature%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20look%20like%20a%20strawberry%20at%20first.%20But%20if%20you%20zoom%20in%20on%20its%20body%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20tiny%20nub%20at%20the%20apex%20of%20all%20those%20arms%20%E2%80%94%20it%20resembles%20the%20size%20and%20shape%20of%20the%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223965%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Close%20up%20of%20Antarctic%20strawberry%20feather%20star%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d6e4d85e5d5a00195cc188%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222289%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20close-up%20of%20the%20Antarctic%20strawberry%20feather%20star%20with%20some%20of%20the%20cirri%20removed%20to%20unveil%20a%20strawberry-like%20base.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Greg%20W.%20Rouse%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20circular%20bumps%20on%20the%20star's%20body%20are%20where%20the%20cirri%20%E2%80%94%20the%20smaller%20tentacle-like%20strings%20protruding%20from%20the%20base%20%E2%80%94%20should%20be%2C%20but%20were%20removed%20to%20show%20the%20attachment%20points%2C%20Rouse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20taken%20away%20a%20bunch%20of%20the%20cirri%20so%20you%20can%20see%20the%20parts%20that%20they're%20attached%20to%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20looks%20like%20a%20strawberry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20cirri%20have%20tiny%20claws%20at%20the%20end%20that%20are%20used%20to%20hold%20onto%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20seafloor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20so-called%20arms%20are%20the%20longer%2C%20feathery-like%20parts%20of%20the%20Antarctic%20strawberry%20feather%20star%20shown%20in%20the%20image.%20They're%20typically%20spread%20out%2C%20Rouse%20said%2C%20and%20help%20with%20the%20creature's%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20formal%20name%20of%20the%20newfound%20species%20is%20Promachocrinus%20fragarius.%20It%20belongs%20under%20the%20class%20of%20Crinoidea%2C%20which%20includes%20starfish%2C%20sea%20urchins%2C%20sand%20dollars%2C%20and%20sea%20cucumbers%2C%20and%20is%20a%20type%20of%20feather%20star%20%E2%80%94%20hence%20the%20less%20formal%20%26quot%3BAntarctic%20feather%20star%26quot%3B%20name.%20Fragarius%20derives%20from%20the%20Latin%20word%20%26quot%3Bfragum%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20strawberry%2C%20according%20to%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20professor%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20that%20there%20was%20originally%20only%20one%20species%20under%20the%20Antarctic%20feather%20star%20group%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Promachocrinus%20kerguelensis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Promachocrinus%20kerguelensis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d700a91f51cc00196845b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221789%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Promachocrinus%20kerguelnsis%20was%20originally%20thought%20to%20be%20the%20only%20species%20under%20the%20Promachocrinus%20genus.%20%3Cp%3EEric%20A.%20Lazo-Wasem%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20dragging%20a%20net%20along%20the%20Southern%20Ocean%20searching%20for%20more%20samples%20of%20these%20creatures%2C%20the%20team%20of%20scientists%20from%20Australia%20and%20the%20US%20identified%20four%20new%20species%20that%20can%20fall%20under%20the%20Antarctic%20feather%20star%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Antarctic%20strawberry%20feather%20star%20stands%20out%20in%20particular%20due%20to%20the%20number%20of%20%26quot%3Barms%26quot%3B%20it%20has.%20%26quot%3BA%20majority%20of%20feather%20stars%20have%2010%20arms%2C%26quot%3B%20Rouse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERouse%20added%20that%20the%20typical%20position%20of%20a%20feather%20star%20is%20to%20have%20the%20%26quot%3Barms%26quot%3B%20spread%20out%20and%20upward%2C%20while%20the%20cirri%20are%20pointed%20downward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20da