Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Findustry-s-ev-sales-could-rise-by-10-times-in-5-years-says-tata-motors-123081100809_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Findustry-s-ev-sales-could-rise-by-10-times-in-5-years-says-tata-motors-123081100809_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amid%20Impending%20Regional%20Military%20Intervention%2C%20India%20Asks%20Citizens%20to%20Leave%20Niger%20Immediately%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11222707%2FF3NIO1MXcAEQvvL.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20has%20issued%20an%20advisory%20for%20Indian%20citizens%20to%20leave%20Niger%2C%20which%20witnessed%20a%20military%20coup%20three%20weeks%20ago.%20There%20are%20indications%20that%20the%20regional%20bloc%20of%20the%20Economic%20Community%20of%20West%20African%20States%20(ECOWAS)%20is%20gearing%20up%20for%20a%20military%20intervention%20in%20the%20west%20African%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Government%20of%20India%20is%20closely%20monitoring%20ongoing%20developments%20in%20Niger.%20In%20light%20of%20the%20prevailing%20situation%2C%20Indian%20nationals%20whose%20presence%20is%20not%20essential%20are%20advised%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37006%2FAdvisory%2Bfor%2BIndian%2Bnationals%2Bin%2BNiger%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20advisory%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20around%20250%20Indian%20citizens%20residing%20in%20Niger%20currently%2C%20as%20per%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%2C%20who%20urged%20them%20all%20to%20remain%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20Indian%20embassy%20and%20find%20ways%20to%20leave%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20may%20bear%20in%20mind%20that%20air%20space%20is%20currently%20closed.%20When%20departing%20through%20a%20land%20border%2C%20utmost%20precautions%20may%20be%20taken%20to%20ensure%20safety%20and%20security%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20advisory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20MEA%20is%20advising%20individuals%20who%20might%20have%20upcoming%20travel%20plans%20to%20Niger%20in%20the%20near%20future%20to%20reconsider%20their%20arrangements%20until%20the%20situation%20returns%20to%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20Indian%20nationals%20who%20have%20not%20registered%20with%20the%20Indian%20Embassy%20in%20Niamey%20are%20strongly%20advised%20to%20do%20so%20promptly.%20The%20emergency%20contact%20of%20the%20Indian%20mission%20at%20Niamey%20is%20%2B227-9975%209975.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%20on%20July%2026%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Niger%E2%80%99s%20presidential%20guard%2C%20General%20Abdourahmane%20Tchiani%2C%20ousted%20President%20Mohamed%20Bazoum%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20regional%20bloc%20Economic%20Community%20of%20West%20African%20States%20(ECOWAS)%20imposing%20sanctions%20and%20closing%20borders.%20It%20was%20the%20seventh%20coup%20in%20West%20and%20Central%20Africa%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fniger-coup-west-africa-bfd1ddcf075379289475d3f72d85fa16%5C%22%3EECOWAS%20announced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20had%20ordered%20the%20activation%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98standby%20force%E2%80%99%20to%20deploy%20in%20the%20west%20African%20country.%20The%20regional%20organisation%20had%20given%20a%20deadline%20till%20last%20Sunday%20for%20the%20reinstatement%20of%20President%20Bazoum%2C%20whose%20life%20has%20been%20threatened%20by%20the%20coup%20leaders.%20The%20African%20Union%20has%20supported%20ECOWAS%E2%80%99s%20decision%20and%20called%20for%20the%20immediate%20release%20of%20Bazoum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20still%20not%20clear%20when%20the%20military%20force%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20Niger.%20Ivory%20Coast%20president%20Alassane%20Ouattara%20announced%20that%20he%20will%20be%20sending%20soldiers%20for%20the%20military%20operation%2C%20along%20with%20Benin%20and%20Nigeria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20military%20junta%20organised%20massive%20rallies%20in%20the%20capital%20Niamey%20in%20support%20of%20the%20coup%2C%20which%20was%20attended%20by%20a%20large%20number%20of%20citizens%2C%20fuelled%20by%20anti-French%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAP%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20hundreds%20of%20people%20marched%20toward%20the%20French%20military%20base%20in%20Niamey%20on%20Friday%20waving%20Russian%20flags%20and%20screaming%20%E2%80%9CDown%20with%20France%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691773351000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11222707%2FF3NIO1MXcAEQvvL.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Famid-impending-regional-military-intervention-india-asks-citizens-to-leave-niger-immediately%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20around%20250%20Indian%20citizens%20residing%20in%20the%20west%20African%20country%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Famid-impending-regional-military-intervention-india-asks-citizens-to-leave-niger-immediately%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Special%20counsel%20to%20investigate%20President%20Biden's%20son%20Hunter%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691772805000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F83B3%2Fproduction%2F_115651733_breaking-large-promo-nc.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66480353%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20prosecutor%20who%20brought%20c